]]. {{citation needed|date=November 2014}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://votebishop.com/ Rob Bishop for Congress]\n* {{Dmoz|Regional/North_America/United_States/Utah/Government/Federal/US_House_of_Representatives/Rob_Bishop_%5BR-1%5D|Rob Bishop}}\n* {{C-SPAN|Rob Bishop}}\n{{CongLinks | congbio = b001250 | ballot = Rob_Bishop | nndb = 368/000032272 | votesmart = 50544 | govtrack = 400029 | opencong = 400029 | rollcall = 15463 | politifact = | fec = H2UT01094 | opensecrets = N00025292 | assets = rob-bishop | legistorm = 126/Rep_Rob_Bishop.html | followthemoney = 118382 | ontheissues = House/Rob_Bishop.htm | congress = rob-bishop/1753 | worldcat = | cspan = 1003621 | imdb = 3870411 | bloomberg = | nyt = | wsj = | washpo = gIQALHQPAP }}\n;Articles\n* {{YouTube|QSCk4jomfWc|Bishop promotes oil shale exploration}}{{when|date=August 2013}}\n* {{YouTube|voV5fvOEA5s|Bishop Denies Tax Breaks for Oil Companies}}{{when|date=August 2013}}\n* {{YouTube|sa5cFZzoh_A|Bishop Backtracks on subsidies question}}{{when|date=August 2013}}\n* [http://www.deseretnews.com/article/700114283/Dont-cut-conservation-programs.html/ Bishop supports cutting conservation programs] \u2018\u2019Deseret News\u2019\u2019{{when|date=August 2013}}\n* [http://www.deseretnews.com/article/705366847/Groups-blast-Bishop-over-gutting-landscape-conservation.html/ Bishop Criticized for not Supporting conservation programs] \u2018\u2019Deseret News\u2019\u2019{{when|date=August 2013}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[James V. Hansen|James Hansen]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[List of United States Representatives from Utah|U.S. House of Representatives]]<br>from [[Utah's 1st congressional district]]|years=2003\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc|rows=2}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Doc Hastings]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Chair of the [[United States House Committee on Natural Resources|House Natural Resources Committee]]|years=2015\u2013present}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|usa}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Joe Wilson (U.S. politician)|Joe Wilson]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Seniority in the United States House of Representatives|United States Representatives by seniority]]|years=113th}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Marsha Blackburn]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{UT-FedRep}}\n{{USHouseCurrent}}\n{{USHouseChairs}}\n{{US House Natural Resources chairs}}\n{{UtahUSRepresenatives}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bishop, Rob}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century Mormon missionaries]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:American educators]]\n[[Category:American Latter Day Saints]]\n[[Category:American lobbyists]]\n[[Category:American Mormon missionaries in Germany]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the United States House of Representatives from Utah]]\n[[Category:Members of the Utah House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:People from Davis County, Utah]]\n[[Category:People from Brigham City, Utah]]\n[[Category:Republican Party members of the United States House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:Speakers of the Utah House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:State political party chairs of Utah]]\n[[Category:Tea Party movement activists]]\n[[Category:Utah Republicans]]\n[[Category:University of Utah alumni]]"}]}}}}